{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "To ensure volunteers who dress up for charity organisations have DBS checks",
        "additional_details": "At the moment any sex offenders even if they are on the sex offenders registry are allowed to dress in costume concealing their identity and carry out non-profit charity work even at events where children could be present and interacted with without any DBS checks. I would like a law to be passed to make such organisations responsible to carry out DBS checks on any present and new members by law",
        "background": "Organisations (non-profit) who do charity events are not as yet required by law to give members DBS checks",
